-- Stoke Signs Ex-England Striker Owen to One-Year Deal
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-09-05T03:25:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-04/stoke-signs-former-england-striker-michael-owen-to-one-year-deal.html
(Corrects Owen’s position on England’s goal-scorers’ list
to fourth in story published yesterday.)  Stoke signed former England striker
 Michael Owen  to a one-year contract, pending approval from the
Premier League board, the club said on its website.  Owen, 32, was a free agent after being released by
Manchester United at the end of last season. He’s scored 221
goals in 473 games during his career with Liverpool, Real
Madrid, Newcastle and United.  Owen also has 40 goals in 89 games for England, ranking
fourth all-time for the country behind  Bobby Charlton ’s 49, Gary Lineker’s 48 and Jimmy Greaves’s 44.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  